.mailchimp.com/13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0/images/097215bc-68e2-44b2-a9b4-15fddb6b3b06.png" style="opacity: 0.9;font-family: tahoma, verdana, segoe, sans-serif;font-size: 17.7777786254883px;line-height: 1.6em;width: 20px;height: 20px;margin: 0px 0px -3px;border: 0;outline: none;text-decoration: none;" width="20">&nbsp; &nbsp;<img align="none" height="21" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0/images/f3287432-f4f9-4f0a-8fa1-89813f0c78d3.png" style="opacity: 0.9;line-height: 20.7999992370605px;width: 20px;height: 21px;margin: 0px;border: 0;outline: none;text-decoration: none;" width="20">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Create an application that will display the number of kilometers per liter (output) based on the number of miles per gallon (input). Make sure to round off the result to two decimal points. &nbsp;<a href="http://codewars.us5.list-manage.com/track/click?u=13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0&id=0f3b4b8444&e=03671ad129" target="_blank" style="color: #cb3d2b;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: none;word-wrap: break-word !important;">&nbsp;ftopower</a><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<img align="none" height="26" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0/images/7_kyu.png" style="opacity: 0.9;font-family: tahoma, verdana, segoe, sans-serif;font-size: 12px;line-height: 20.7999992370605px;width: 50px;height: 26px;margin: 0px;border: 0;outline: none;text-decoration: none;" width="50"><a href="http://codewars.us5.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0&id=d2c76190bc&e=03671ad129" target="_blank" style="color: #cb3d2b;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: none;word-wrap: break-word !important;"><span style="font-size:16px">makeBackronym</span></a>&nbsp; &nbsp;<img align="none" height="20" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0/images/prog_js02_red_01.1.png" style="opacity: 0.9;font-family: tahoma, verdana, segoe, sans-serif;font-size: 17.7777786254883px;line-height: 1.6em;width: 20px;height: 20px;margin: 0px 0px 