 Instead of cutting the string from the end, your function will shorten it from the middle like shrinking. &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://codewars.us5.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0&id=5c94f205ae&e=03671ad129" target="_blank" style="color: #cb3d2b;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: none;word-wrap: break-word !important;">serkanyersen</a><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<span style="line-height:20.7999992370605px"><img align="none" height="26" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0/images/5_kyu.png" style="width: 50px;height: 26px;margin: 0px;border: 0;line-height: 100%;outline: none;text-decoration: none;" width="50">&nbsp; &nbsp;<span style="font-size:16px"><a href="http://codewars.us5.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0&id=03077e4076&e=03671ad129" target="_blank" style="color: #cb3d2b;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: none;word-wrap: break-word !important;">Merged String Checker&nbsp;&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;</span></span><img align="none" height="20" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0/images/prog_js02_red_01.1.png" style="opacity: 0.9;font-family: tahoma, verdana, segoe, sans-serif;font-size: 17.7777786254883px;line-height: 1.6em;width: 20px;height: 20px;margin: 0px 0px -3px;border: 0;outline: none;text-decoration: none;" width="20">&nbsp; &nbsp;<img align="none" height="20" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0/images/prog_ruby_red_01.png" style="opacity: 0.9;line-height: 20.7999992370605px;width: 20px;height: 20px;margin: 0px 0px -2px;border: 0;outline: none;text-decoration: none;" width="20">&nbsp; &nbsp;<img align="none" height="20" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13bbf05035a7fd3e5b7abcdf0/images/prog_coffeescr_red_01.png" style="opacity: 0.9;line-height: 20.7999992370605px;width: 20px;height: 20px;margin: 0px 0px -3px;border: 0;outline: none;text-decoration: none;" width="20">&nbsp; &nbsp;<img align="none" height="20" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13bbf05035